{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, each additional run ensures better confidence in the extracted events, as results are aggregated: we assign the final result if it was confirmed in at least 2 across all 4 runs.",
    "For example, in the following 4 inferences of a single social history note, the algorithm picks only the label \"married\" with a year of event 2021 since the date for \"arrest\" couldn't be successfully determined in at least two runs: Run (1) Married (2021).",
    "Run (2) Arrest (2018), Married (2021).",
    "Run (3) No events detected.",
    "Run (4) Arrest (recent event).The diagram depicting the steps of note processing and inference is presented in Supplement C. Figure 2."
  ]
}